<br>
I have recieved this poem around 3 times in my years, always with some sort of BS chain letter crap on the end.  Anybody who has dealt with that over and over can empathize with Kelisk for his initial annoyance at the poem.<br>
<br>
Is this poem meant to create an emotional response in the reader?  Yes.  Was this poem written for the explicit purpose of being used in conjunction with chain emails?  Probably not.  Does this poem convey a message?  NO!!!<br>
<br>
This poem conveys NO message.  Anybody who reads this poem, and then decides that rather than being 100% OK to do, that drinking and driving is a bad idea, is a retard.  Actually no, because even retards have some concept and awareness of reality.  To think that it conveys a message is the same ignorant thinking of putting warning labels on cigarrette boxes.  No human being in history looked at a box of cigarettes and said &quot;holy crap these are bad for me&quot; and then quit.<br>
<br>
